Name: Description
Child Population by Race/Ethnicity: Population for children under 18 years by racial/ethnic group.

Name: Source Notes
Child Population by Race/Ethnicity: CCC analysis of U.S. Census Bureau, American Community Survey 1-Year Estimates, Public Use Microdata Sample File (2005-2018); retrieved from https://data.census.gov/.

Name: Notes
Child Population by Race/Ethnicity: Percents refer to the percent of all children under 18 years. Racial/ethnic groups are defined as follows: White = non-Latino White alone, Black = non-Latino Black alone, Asian = non-Latino Asian or Pacific Islander alone, Latino = Latino of any race.
